Advanced Practice Registered Nurse or Nurse-Practitioner &#8211; A person who is licensed to practice as a registered nurse pursuant to the District of Columbia Health Occupations Revision Act of 1985, effective March 25, 1986 (D.C. Law 6-99;
      D.C. Official Code § 3-1201 et seq.), and meets the additional licensure requirements for practice in a particular area as an advance practice registered nurse or nurse- practitioner in accordance with D.C. Official Code § 3-1206.08(a) or (c), or
      is licensed as a registered nurse and meets additional national certification standards for practice in a particular area as an advance practice registered nurse or nurse- practitioner in the jurisdiction where services are provided.
